        DESCRIPTION:
          " <br/>Dear Violeta,<br/> <br/>We spoke on the phone few minutes ago, please check our fabrics, reflective<br/>tapes e- catalogs. I am sales manager Donata Litvaitiene, please write if<br/>you will be interested in our XM Textiles fabrics and reflective tapes I<br/>will send all our catalogs for your company. <br/> <br/>Please see attached our company profile.<br/> <br/>For your information, I would like to mention to you that our company<br/>specializes in a wide range of work wear fabrics: 100% polyester fabrics, TC<br/>fabrics (cotton blend with Polyester content &gt;50%), CVC fabrics (cotton<br/>blend with Polyester &lt; 50%) and 100% cotton fabrics. All XM Textiles fabrics<br/>are suitable for sewing work wear for almost any industry.<br/> <br/>Within XM Textiles we&#039;ve got two innovative brands -<br/> XM FireLine and   XM<br/>SilverLine.<br/>  XM Fireline is a brand created to meet the needs<br/>for fabrics with special characteristics, such as flame retardant,<br/>antistatic, oil, water and acid repellent fabrics. All the products of this<br/>line are tested in laboratory before shipment for their accordance to ISO<br/>standards (for example, ISO 105 C06-2010 C2S for color fastness to washing,<br/>ISO 13937:2-2000 - for tearing strength).<br/>All flame retardant fabrics were tested and certified according to ISO<br/>11612:2008 (Protective clothing -- Clothing to protect against heat and<br/>flame). All fabrics of XM Fireline have certificates from the leading<br/>laboratory, BTTG (UK) that specialises in the field of labor<br/>protection(PPE). Besides, our flame retardant fabrics are passed very<br/>thorough American test - ASTM 1959 (Test for Electric Arc) which is<br/>conducted by Kinetrics laboratory(Canada). Our FR fabrics keep their<br/>anti-static properties after numerous repeated washings (100x and more).<br/> <br/>In Fire Line we  have new flame retardant aramid fabrics which go under<br/>ARTEX line.<br/>Flame Retardant ArTex collection fabrics are made of blended aramid fibers<br/>in composition of Meta - Aramid, Para - Aramid and Antistatic fibers. The<br/>aramid fibers are inherently flame retardant and don&#039;t melt. The composition<br/>of ArTex fabrics is similar to the well - know aramid fabric NOMEX IIIA is<br/>93% meta - aramid, 5% para - aramid - 2% antistatic. When exposed to intense<br/>heat, the fiber carbonizes and becomes thicker, forming a protective barrier<br/>between the heat source and the skin. This protective barrier stays supple<br/>and flexible until it cools, giving the wearer extra seconds of protection.<br/> <br/>XM Silverline is a brand embracing different kinds of reflective materials<br/>for increasing safety in industrial work wear, for high-visibility clothes<br/>on roads and in other environments where a high-visibility is a key issue of<br/>safety at work.<br/> <br/>For more information please kindly visit our websites:<br/> <br/>  www.xmtextiles.com<br/>- Basic Work wear Fabrics<br/>  www.xmfireline.com<br/> - Flame Retardant  Fabrics<br/>  www.xmsilverline.com<br/> - Hi-Viz Reflective Tapes<br/> <br/> <br/>Should you have any further queries please do not hesitate to contact me<br/> <br/>Best regards,<br/> Donata<br/> <br/> <br/>Description: aplusa_footer_2015",
